-- Syracuse Defeats Wisconsin 64-63 in NCAA Basketball Tournament
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-03-23T01:24:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/syracuse-defeats-wisconsin-64-63-in-ncaa-basketball-tournament.html
C.J. Fair scored 15 points and top-
seeded Syracuse held on for a 64-63 victory against fourth-
seeded  Wisconsin  to reach the East Regional final of the men’s
national college basketball tournament.  Jordan Taylor, who had 17 points, six assists and four
rebounds for Wisconsin (26-10), missed a long 3-pointer in the
closing seconds of the National Collegiate Athletic Association
game at the TD Garden in  Boston .  Scoop Jardine had 14 points for Syracuse (34-2), which
moved on to face Cincinnati or Ohio State in the regional final.
Syracuse led by 10 points in the first half and by 33-27 at
halftime.  “That’s the best game I’ve seen in a long time, that may
be the best game we’ve played,” Syracuse coach  Jim Boeheim  said
in a televised interview. “I can’t tell you how good it feels
to win, this was a great game.”  Jared Berggren added 17 points for Wisconsin, which went
14-for-27 on 3-pointers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
